Method Detail

onItemSelected

public void onItemSelected( parent,
                           View v,
                           int pos,
                           long row)
When the user selects an item in the spinner, this method is invoked by the callback chain. Android calls the item selected listener for the spinner, which invokes the onItemSelected method.

Parameters:
parent - - the AdapterView for this listener
v - - the View for this listener
pos - - the 0-based position of the selection in the mLocalAdapter
row - - the 0-based row number of the selection in the View
See Also:
android.widget.AdapterView.OnItemSelectedListener#onItemSelected( android.widget.AdapterView, android.view.View, int, long)

onNothingSelected

public void onNothingSelected( parent)
The definition of OnItemSelectedListener requires an override of onNothingSelected(), even though this implementation does not use it.

Parameters:
parent - - The View for this Listener
